title: Kinect Sports: Season Two
description: The Games on Demand version supports  English, French, Italian, German, Spanish, Portuguese, Russian, Japanese, Korean and Chinese. This game requires a Kinect™ Sensor.  Kinect Sports: Season Two sprints out of the box at full speed, taking full advantage of the revolutionary Kinect technology and its latest exciting features like in-game voice commands and enhanced motion tracking.  Bringing the family together, and introducing Challenge Play to Xbox LIVE and living rooms worldwide, Kinect Sports: Season Two harnesses the power of friendly competition to provide a more immersive experience for everyone from casual players to top-notch athletes and hardcore sports fans.

childDownloads.title: Kinect Sports Season 2 – Maple Lakes Trailer
childDownloads.description: The ‘Maple Lakes’ golf pack expands your Kinect Sports: Season Two golf experience by adding 9 new holes into the mix!   Swing to win past forts, marinas, causeways and coves, finding hidden routes and hole-in-one opportunities. Attempt an 18-hole course match, the ultimate Golfing gauntlet!

childDownloads.title: Kinect Sports Season 2 - Midnight Mountain Trailer
childDownloads.description: Throwing yourself downhill in broad daylight not exciting enough? These new floodlit Skiing runs for Kinect Sports: Season Two will get your heart racing. Midnight Mountain's three icy cool slopes are playable in all modes with new challenges to send to friends. Check them out in the trailer!

childDownloads.title: Kinect Sports: Season Two Depth Video
childDownloads.description: The sequel to the best-selling sports game on Kinect launches October 25th, 2011!  Take a peek behind-the-scene as the game developers show you what is coming in this ground-breaking interactive experience. Kinect Sports: Season Two, the top-selling Kinect game returns with six new sports, including Football, Skiing, Baseball, Darts, Golf and Tennis.  And now, with in-game voice control.  Experience the thrill of full-body control – plus, now for the first time you can use your voice to advance the game:  call plays in football, ask your caddy for golf clubs, and more. Kinect Sports: Season Two – only on Kinect for Xbox 360.
